### 2.1 Customer Specific System Details

#### 2.1.1 Scope Selection

First, options that have sales/stock transaction in the last 3 months are selected. Then option-country level warehouse stocks are calculated. Broken options ( Less that %80 of sizes are available at the warehouse) enter the algorithm directly. For non-broken options, warehouse stock threshold defined by UI is checked. Default warehouse stock threshold is 30. That means options that have more than 30 warehouse stock do not enter the transfer scope. Lastly stocked days of each product-store pairs are calculated. Pairs that have 0 stocked days in the last 90 days are eliminated from the scope. These selection/elimination rules also apply for the product selection from UI. Outcome pairs enter the transfer algorithm.

tion rules also apply for the product selection from UI. Outcome pairs enter the transfer algorithm.

Link for customer specific scope selection sp : [GetTransferProductsStores](https://gitlab.com/invent-analytics/maps-database/-/blob/master/CustomerSpecific/ApparelGroup/ApparelGroup.Maps.Database/transfer/Stored%20Procedures/GetTransferProductsStores.sql)

#### 2.1.2 Store & Shipment Capacities

No store or shipment capacity rules

#### 2.1.3 Min-Max Rules

All pairs that have positive sales in the last 90 days have a minimum-1-stock threshold. These pairs are selected with the [get_min_max_thresholds.py](https://gitlab.com/invent-analytics/pipeline/apparelgroup/-/blob/master/scripts/transfer/get_min_max_thresholds.py#L162) code and inserted in `transfer.MinimumStockThresholdsByPair` in DB.

/get_min_max_thresholds.py#L162) code and inserted in `transfer.MinimumStockThresholdsByPair` in DB.

Maximum thresholds are calculated for pairs that have positive sales/stock in the last 90 days. First the algorithm gets the latest 28 data points for each pair. If the current store stock is more than the 28 days sales amount then the store stock becomes the maximum threshold else sales amount becomes the maximum threshold. For pairs that have less than 28 data points sales quantity is expanded accordingly. These thresholds are calculated with the [get_min_max_thresholds.py](https://gitlab.com/invent-analytics/pipeline/apparelgroup/-/blob/master/scripts/transfer/get_min_max_thresholds.py#L78) code and inserted in `transfer.MaximumStockThresholdsByPair` in DB.

#### 2.1.4 Blocking Rules

#L78) code and inserted in `transfer.MaximumStockThresholdsByPair` in DB.

#### 2.1.4 Blocking Rules

Pairs that are transferred out in the last 15 days + pairs that have no sales in the last 90 days are destination blocked. These pairs are selected with the [get_blocked_pairs.py](https://gitlab.com/invent-analytics/pipeline/apparelgroup/-/blob/master/scripts/transfer/get_blocked_pairs.py#L76) code and inserted in `transfer.BlockedDestinationsByProduct`in DB.

Pairs that are transferred-in in the last 15 days + pairs that have their first sales in the last 30 days (new products in the stores) are origin blocked. These pairs are selected with the [get_blocked_pairs.py](https://gitlab.com/invent-analytics/pipeline/apparelgroup/-/blob/master/scripts/transfer/get_blocked_pairs.py#L156) code and inserted in `transfer.BlockedOriginsByProduct`in DB.

#### 2.1.5 Results Sharing

Selected transfer results are shared in S3/invent-apparelgroup-output bucket. Both customer and Invent can reach/edit this bucket. Executed run results are moved to History bucked by customer.

### 2.4 PreProcess & PostProcess

#### PreProcess

- Sets ReuseLatForecastForTransfer parameter as True. This is needed since the MAPS FC module is out of use and forecasts are generated via noob.
- Updates transfer.StockDatesByRun table: Why?Due to delays in data transfer (as of 9.28.2021, max inventory position date is 9.26.2021), we needed to log the max date of inventory position to better understand results or even use it when generating Transfer KPI Reporting data.To better understand which stock-date is used by Run, such a table is created

```
update engine.RunParametersset Value = 'True'
where Name= 'ReuseLastForecastForTransfer' and runId = @RunId

-- record max date in inventory position when run started

DECLARE @MaxDate as date
SET @MaxDate  = (select MAX(Date) from data.InventoryPosition where StoreStock > 0)
DECLARE @StockDate Date =COALESCE(IIF(@TransferTargetDate >= @MaxDate,@MaxDate,@MaxDate),@MaxDate)

)
DECLARE @StockDate Date =COALESCE(IIF(@TransferTargetDate >= @MaxDate,@MaxDate,@MaxDate),@MaxDate)

INSERT INTO transfer.StockDatesByRun  (RunId,StockDate) VALUES(@RunId,@StockDate)
```

#### PostProcess

- Deletes transfer decisions where the total transfer quantity between two nodes is less than the given Minimum Transfer Amount (via UI)Consolidation and clearance runs are exempt from such deletion
- Generates transfer detailed results.

```
EXEC tableau.TransferPostprocessOrderDeletion @RunId
EXEC tableau.GenerateTransferDetailedResults  @TransferRunId = @RunId
```

#### 2.10.1 Transfer Results Control

It is a report where the detailed information about products transferred from source stores to the destination stores, sales performance of the stores and the stock status before and after the transfer can be examined. It is updated after each transfer run.

[TransferResultControl](https://apparelgroup.next.inventanalytics.com/reports/TransferResultControl/TransferControl)

#### 2.10.2 Transfer Store Performance Comparison

It is a report in which the sales-stock performance of a product at the source and destination stores can be examined retrospectively. The desired pairs can be checked by entering the product and store codes in the parameter boxes.

[StorePerformanceComparison](https://apparelgroup.next.inventanalytics.com/reports/StorePerformanceComparison/TransferStorePerformances)

#### 2.10.3 Store SKU Historic Data

m/reports/StorePerformanceComparison/TransferStorePerformances)

#### 2.10.3 Store SKU Historic Data

It is a report in which the sales-stock-warehouse stock performance of a product-store pairs can be examined retrospectively. The desired pairs can be checked by entering the product and store codes in the parameter boxes. Outlier sales are also observable in this report.

[StoreProductHistoricalData](https://apparelgroup.next.inventanalytics.com/reports/StoreProductHistoricalData/StoreProductHistoricData)

cs.com/reports/StoreProductHistoricalData/StoreProductHistoricData)

#### 2.10.4 Availability Report

In this report store and product based end-of-day availability can be examined. The scope is all pairs that have stock or sales in last 150 days. Products that have currently 0 store or warehouse inventory at country level are eliminated. It is updated after daily data transfer. The source data of this report is generated by [availability_report.py](https://gitlab.com/invent-analytics/pipeline/apparelgroup/-/blob/master/scripts/reporting/availability_report.py)

### 3.3 Default Region-Scenario System

In default scenario stores in the same country belong to one region and between regions the transfer is prohibited by defining too high distances between stores in different countries. The distances are assigned in `[transfer].[UpdateTransferStoreDistances]` sp.

### 3.4 Broken Assortment System

es are assigned in `[transfer].[UpdateTransferStoreDistances]` sp.

### 3.4 Broken Assortment System

Apparelgroup uses weighted broken assortment in transfer optimization. The weight of each SKU of an option is calculated considering it's sales quantity within the last 90 days. Minimum broken ratio rate is %60 in default. Broken assortment weight are calculated in transfer daily dag by [get_broken_weights.py](https://gitlab.com/invent-analytics/pipeline/apparelgroup/-/blob/master/scripts/transfer/get_broken_weights.py) and insert into `transfer.BrokenAssortmentProductWeights`. Details of the weighted broken assortment system can be found here: [MAPS Transfer System]

### 3.5 Run Frequency & Schedule

Apparelgroup did not require any scheduled automatic transfer run. Users take ad-hoc runs.

Interpretation of example mail:

The important points to consider and control in the result of transfer algorithm are as follows

- Transfer quantity
- Store region scenario
- Run type
- Duration
- Infeasible naive model ratio
- Transferred stock ratio
- Number of origin/destination storesForecast Input/Output Product/Store Count

A naive model created by transfer algorithm is said to be infeasible if there is no solution which satisfies all the constraints. If the infeasible naive model ratio is bigger than 50 %, one should find out the reason for this.

- Broken assortment weights of products in the result of the model should be controlled. Minimum broken ratio rate is %60 in default. Therefore, the weighted broken assortment of each available SKU and if 60% or more of the selected product can be collected in a store must be checked. (see this page for more information!)
- Another possible reason that causes infeasible result is that the transfer algorithm cannot find a solution if a high weighted SKU of the product does not have enough store stock. (improve weight assignment algorithm)
- Checking if stores selected by the user are on the transfer.BlockedDestinationsByProduct is also significant in such cases. One way to check this is to delete the relevant constraints about destination blockage rule from the model and re-execute it. If the model finds a solution, that means the stores are on the transfer.BlockedDestinationsByProduct.
- Lastly, minimum & maximum stocks of the product must be controlled.

If the infeasible models ratio is high for a run, it should decrease after re-run the algorithm with the solve infeasible models parameter. If it is increased, we can look at the transfer.InfeasibleSolverModelstable to see if there are more than one record with the same infeasible model name on it. The reason for this increase can be that the algorithm cannot solve the infeasible models in the second iteration. Therefore, we need to check the number of models which are infeasible after the second iteration is less than or equal to the number of the infeasible models for the first iteration. To do so, the following queries can be used.

```
  SELECT COUNT(*) FROM transfer.InfeasibleSolverModels IM
  WHERE IM.RunId=10824
  SELECT COUNT(*) FROM transfer.InfeasibleSolverModels IM
  WHERE IM.RunId=10826
  AND ModelKey like '%_SecondTry%'
```

If a product does not have sufficient stock, this may have caused infeasible results. We made a development for this case, and we define the minimum stock threshold if the total stock of the product in the stores is greater than 30 in the [get_min_max_threshold.py](https://gitlab.com/invent-analytics/pipeline/apparelgroup/-/blob/master/scripts/transfer/get_min_max_thresholds.py#L182) script.

- General Monthly Summary: The Monthly Summary table is displayed in this section.The important point here is to look at the filters at the bottom of the slide in the presentation and then check if the filters mentioned are applied on the tableau. For example, if there is a 1% filter on the executed ratio under the general monthly summary slide, we go to the tableau and check the filters on the right. The meaning of putting a 1% filter on the run execution ratio is as follows: the individual execution rates of the runs are examined and if they are less than 1%, they are not added to the report.Since the last two months are not of interest, the last two months are not included in the presentation because there is an 8-week observation period after the transfer.
